Aim:
To implement control flow statements and looping statements in python.

Algorithm:
Step 1: Start the program.

Step 2: Read the number of players pl from the user.

Step 3: Use a for loop to repeat the process for each player from 1 to pl.

Step 4: Display the player number.

Step 5: Accept the following inputs for each player:

Runs scored

Number of balls faced

Number of fours scored

Number of sixes scored

Number of wickets taken

Runs conceded

Number of overs bowled

Number of catches taken

Step 6: Calculate the Strike Rate (sr) using the formula:
sr = (Runs / balls) × 100

Step 7: Calculate the Economy Rate (er) using the formula:
er = runs conceded / overs

Step 8: Determine the Batting Performance:

If runs ≥ 50 and strike rate ≥ 120 → "Excellent Batter"

Else if runs ≥ 30 and strike rate ≥ 100 → "Good Batter"

Else if runs ≥ 20 → "Average Batter"

Otherwise → "Poor Batter"

Step 9: Determine the Bowling Performance:

If wickets ≥ 3 and economy rate ≤ 6 → "Excellent Bowler"

Else if wickets ≥ 2 and economy rate ≤ 8 → "Good Bowler"

Else if wickets ≥ 1 → "Average Bowler"

Otherwise → "Poor Bowler"

Step 10: Determine the Fielding Performance:

If catches ≥ 2 → "Outstanding Fielder"

Else if catches = 1 → "Active Fielder"

Otherwise → "Needs Improvement"

Step 11: Determine the Overall All-Rounder Performance:

If batting = "Excellent Batter" and bowling = "Excellent Bowler" → "Star All-Rounder"

Else if batting = "Good Batter" and bowling = "Good Bowler" → "Strong All-Rounder"

Else if batting = "Good Batter" or bowling = "Good Bowler" → "Supporting All-Rounder"

Otherwise → "Needs Improvement"

Step 12: Display the Strike Rate, Economy Rate, Batting Performance, Bowling Performance, Fielding Performance, and Overall All-Rounder Performance.

Step 13: Repeat the process for all players.

Step 14: Stop the program.
